Package com.APP.Project.UserCoreLogic.responses

Class CommandResponses

java.lang.Object
com.APP.Project.UserCoreLogic.responses.CommandResponses
public class CommandResponses extends Object
Encapsulates the details of a user command issued during the GAME_STATE#GAME_PLAY phase of the game.

This class serves as a container for command information interpreted from user interactions via the UserInterface. It breaks down a user command into its primary component (the head of the command) and any associated values, facilitating further processing or execution of game logic based on the user's input. Additionally, it provides utility methods to determine specific command states, such as whether a player has completed issuing commands.

Version:
1.0
Author:
Bhoomiben Bhatt

    • isDone

      public boolean isDone()
      Determines whether the user command indicates a request to stop issuing further orders. This utility method checks if the head of the command equals "done", signaling that the user wishes to end their command input session.
      Returns:
      true if the user command is "done", indicating no further orders will be issued; otherwise false.
